channel.description:
I've done everything, portfoward, no-ip and no-ip DUC, allowed an exception of 43594 ports UDP and TCP,i have JDK 6u3 and it works proper
Portfoward
[IMG]http://i272.photobucket.com/albums/jj168/Camoboii/Portfoward-1.jpg[/img]
No-ip DUC

It lets people [b] under my internet connection get on using my Computers IP [/b] (the ip that i opened ports for) But it seems that my no-ip is useless and has no effect, how do i make my no-ip work so anyone could connect using my no-ip?

item.title: Having problems with getting my server online
item.dc:creator: @Graham Graham
item.description:
@Graham wrote:

The problem might be your computer’s IP address on the LAN. It’s set to 192.168.0.146.

In command prompt type ipconfig then enter.

Check the IP Address: section. If it’s different, it could have changed or you could have set it wrong.

If it automatically changed, right-click your connection in “Network Connections” (access from control panel) and choose properties. Then, scroll down in the list at the top until you reach “TCP/IP”. Select it, then press properties.

Instead of obtaining addresses automatically, manually type the correct details in.

item.dc:creator: @Graham Graham
item.description:
@Graham wrote:

Go to this site:

http://www.whatsmyip.org/ports/

And use the port “43594” in the custom port scanner while the server is online. If it says OK, it is a problem with no-ip. If not, it’s a problem with your port forwarding. Once you’ve done that we can help you more.
